Comment: 0,0:01:40.78,0:01:40.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.61,0:01:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To arrange a meeting for their parents, \Nthe two gave them both invitations to a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.22,0:01:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, finally, having met in Munich face to face, \Ndad and mom managed to talk peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.94,0:02:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, contrary to Lotte's reckoning, even after that, \Ntheir parents preferred to leave things as they currently are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.76,0:02:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, Luise had become Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.68,0:02:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lotte had also become Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Separately, they return to their alternative lives \Nin Vienna and Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.25,0:02:21.19,Sign,,0,0,115,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 19 \N {\fs35} We Can't Understand Dad!? \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know - \Nour trip to Munich feels like a dream already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.61,0:02:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,After such a long time, \NI was delighted to see Luise and mom again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.71,0:02:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We moved mountains \Nto make dad and mom talk to each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.38,0:02:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, unlike the movies, \Nthey turned it into the least romantic thing ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.79,0:02:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you playing innocent? \NAfter getting this far, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.08,0:02:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell me why, \Nafter bringing me out to a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.00,0:03:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.60,0:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Save your breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's vaunting about his love \Nis what you wanted me to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Vaunting about love?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.60,0:03:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I know exactly why you invited me here - to injure my pride, \Nto humiliate me in the most aggravating manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should come up with some new plan \Nfor drawing them together?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.02,0:03:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Luise, it's just the way you wrote it in your letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.75,0:03:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if she doesn't let it show through, \Nmom still loves dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.50,0:03:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, how do you feel about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.30,0:03:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that, not that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For whatever reason, \NI can't get in the right mood. {/can't focus today}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.36,0:04:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At least one of us \Nis entering the happiest years of his life. {/it seems, you'll be living happily}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.12,0:04:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your mind off this.\NIt's all in a distant past now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We became strangers as soon as we broke up. \NShe can do whatever with her life. Not my concern anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That said...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though she became even prettier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Radiating confidence, livelier than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.22,0:05:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are so alike. \NYou and Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.04,0:05:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, him... I wonder if he is leading a happy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.82,0:05:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he is still just as willful, \Njust as egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of upbringing is he giving to Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he treasuring her more than anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.07,0:05:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that I shouldn't have \Nentrusted him with Luise when we broke up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.53,0:06:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, the bath is vacant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.13,0:06:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.76,0:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I sure am tired today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.31,0:06:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, it was about dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.62,0:06:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand fast on your points, just like in old times. {hard-nosed; strong-willed; determined; unyielding; stubborn; resolute; assertive; headstrong​}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, even more than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.05,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, it was our first meeting in years. \NYou could have shown at least a bit of amiability. {charm; attractiveness; amiability; winsomeness}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no good, no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.11,0:07:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of obsession \Nis a shortcut to becoming neurasthenic. {lit: i don't have the free time to use my delicate nerves on that kind of thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.84,0:07:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,An artist must have a free and unbound mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with no shackle, no chain able to ground me. {/without any limitations}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.81,0:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As my soul is soaring freely through the skies...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.58,0:07:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's so much like dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll catch a cold this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.05,0:08:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the time has not come yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.47,0:08:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! And everything's in a jumble again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.71,0:08:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom's photo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.42,0:08:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,feels this way towards mom? {/no longer loves}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.27,0:08:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy? This is Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.06,0:08:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Frau Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, were you still asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.08,0:08:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.45,0:09:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you finished this latest work of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.32,0:09:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... more or less...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.62,0:09:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean, then, we can pick you up soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.04,0:09:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What for, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.63,0:09:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you managed to forget already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.27,0:09:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, I invited you on a party, held today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's that day already? {/it's today}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to bring Luise along.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.28,0:09:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll meet you outside your house \Nat Rotenturmstraße.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.89,0:09:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.06,0:09:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is bad. \NIt slipped my mind completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.31,0:09:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, what time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, Luise? \NYou're already here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.68,0:09:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Good morning, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you'll say your mornings later, \Nwe need to go to Frau Irene's party now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.96,0:09:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry up to preen yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.06,0:09:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.86,0:09:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally. Now, start moving, \Nlest we'll be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're in a hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.08,0:10:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, make it real quick. \NThey'll come to pick us up any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.59,0:10:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.89,0:10:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, whenever our Master is at home, \Nhe wants everything and at once. {unsure what she means, lit: if you come with ..., suddenly to begin to say; to start talking; to broach (a matter); to bring up; to come out with}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to Frau Gerlach's house... \NWhy should I do it? {/don't want to}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.17,0:10:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going out on a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.37,0:10:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But looking at you, \N one would think you're going on a funeral. {/it'd be better if you make a little more happy face}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems, my head starts to hurt a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.45,0:10:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your head? Hurts bad? {/is it a cold}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.75,0:10:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,For how long? Huh? Temperature...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.65,0:10:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there's anything else wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.25,0:10:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe... I just stay to watch after the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As arranged, I'm here to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.67,0:10:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, sorry for the trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.33,0:10:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, shall we go, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... About that, unfortunately Luise cannot...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.53,0:10:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My, your necktie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.12,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, sorry for the trouble... {no clue what's the first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, if dad goes there alone, it's even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.06,0:11:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I kept you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.36,0:11:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Luise, better already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.18,0:11:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Your head{ache}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.30,0:11:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.63,0:11:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you'll have the pleasure \Nof meeting some of my special guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.30,0:11:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But you still don't mind Luise coming, \Nto such a top-tier party? {unsure what he means: luise getting in the way, was it a good idea - how can she get in the way, in the way of what? fuck knows}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.64,0:11:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt! After all, Luise is my dear friend, \Nand I hope we'll become even closer friends after that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not becoming friends with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.06,0:11:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to use this occasion \Nto finally introduce you, Herr Palfy, to my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.86,0:12:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I was also hoping for a chance \Nto finally get acquainted to your respectable family. {to meet (someone of higher status)​} {I make this sounds specifically misterious to tie up w/ next line}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.21,0:12:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.44,0:12:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, for Luise as well, \N it's a good chance to get used to our company for the future. {unsure: luise, too, will have things to do hereafter - would assume she means "we'll become a family soon"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.93,0:12:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"For the future?" {/hereafter?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.51,0:12:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What can she possibly mean by that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.39,0:12:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a long-awaited guest here, Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You always look after my daughter Irene, \Nwhich I can't help but to appreciate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.27,0:12:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no need... You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, Young Fraulein over here is Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise Palfy, Herr.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been so kind as to invite me. \NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, a little lady, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.36,0:12:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.49,0:12:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.56,0:13:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This old man looks friendly. \NNo wonder he's the owner of the Imperial Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My, isn't that Madame? \NYou finally managed to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.97,0:13:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot for inviting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.00,0:13:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've been terribly busy lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman... \NWhere could I have seen her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.21,0:13:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to introduce. This is my friend, \Na famous Parisian designer, Madame Sharman. {hope it's sharman and not some charlemagne as sharman is mainly an english surname}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.71,0:13:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So she's a famous fashion designer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.91,0:13:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame, this here is composer and conductor, \NHerr Ludwig Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.06,0:13:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My, {\i1}that{\i0} Palfy? \NMay I add that I am highly delighted to meet you? {no clue what's mushi/mushu} {it's the same "being introduced to someone of higher status" as before}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, Madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.90,0:13:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your sublime music that sparks \Nthis inspiration inside me, whenever I need it. {to give (esp. to someone of lower status); to bestow; to grant; to confer; to present; to award}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.47,0:13:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm honored, Madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Meyer, pleased to meet you. One can't help \Nappreciating the distinctive stance that your music has. {lit: has a clear; precise; definite; distinct claim; insistence; assertion; advocacy; emphasis; contention; opinion; tenet}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.38,0:13:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's awe-inspiring!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.44,0:13:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Meyer is a professional architect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had been waiting \Nfor a chance to get introduced to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:13:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, before you - Herr Fischer, the writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really moved by your opera the other day. \NIt was unforgettable. {listening respectfully at the opera house}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I am honored...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why don't you join us in the lounge? {/let's drink over there}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.61,0:14:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.99,0:14:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone here is unbelievably famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad is admired more than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, it feels as if dad somehow got transported \Nto another, completely separate world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.78,0:14:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad now have a personal dad's world all to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.09,0:14:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The world incomprehensible to us children. \NThe grownups' world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.66,0:14:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry, Luise, I had neglected my dear guest! {to leave alone; to leave as is; to ignore; to neglect}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.87,0:14:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come join us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.73,0:14:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are plenty of delicious cakes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.15,0:14:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, don't be shy. {/this way} {acchira?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.40,0:15:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Help yourself to anything you like, Luise. \NLuise, anything caught your eye yet? {suki kashira?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.41,0:15:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are still a good many things \NI need to learn about you, the sooner - the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.68,0:15:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.32,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene, Herr Palfy is a truly amazing gentleman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you! Rumors reach me too, you know.\NAre you two engaged already?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.50,0:15:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, have some patience! \NWe need a little more time. {until engagement}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Engagement?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.91,0:15:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.74,0:15:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't want any.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.47,0:15:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's going on in your world. \NSomething I have no idea about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.38,0:15:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't Luise an adorable child?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.76,0:15:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, she is not making it any easier for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.14,0:15:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She follows Herr Palfy's each step! \NNot every wife can be that clingy. {/like a wife}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.73,0:15:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She is feeling lonely in absence of a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be all right when she starts seeing one in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.86,0:16:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But father, Herr Palfy himself \Nalso clings to his daughter whenever he can!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.03,0:16:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Between me and that girl - \Nwhich one, do you think, is more important?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.27,0:16:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My, your rival is but a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In some ten years, she'll get married off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.21,0:16:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait for that long! \NI want a clear victory, here and now! {/want to make it clear}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only attainable \Nif I make Herr Palfy mine altogether! {/I'll sho you by making ... only mine}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, for how long do you plan to stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go home already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.69,0:16:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is probably having a dinner with mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.42,0:16:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you knew, how much I'm earning \Nto be able to talk to you now... {/how happy that'd make me}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My, this evening air is so refreshing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.78,0:16:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, won't you keep me company? {please sit down; please have a seat​}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.01,0:16:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Herr Palfy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.92,0:16:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.06,0:16:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you intend to keep teaching Luise piano yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.21,0:16:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.51,0:16:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This girl's gift is unquestionable. And it's similar to mine. \NSo I must do my utmost to cultivate it. {to lengthen; to extend; to stretch}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.51,0:17:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My, but I was sure a composer \Nof quite your magnitude
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.59,0:17:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would find a better use for his talent, \Nthan tutoring piano to a little girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.53,0:17:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you believe it's a waste \Nof your precious time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.07,0:17:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A waste? No, don't joke like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.01,0:17:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it be known, \Nthis girl is what my own music originates from! {/on the contrary, she is the source of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, I just think "Luise" and the melody \Nstarts flowing by itself, like from a spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.16,0:17:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.74,0:17:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I guess I'll never be able \Nto become a source for your art, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.04,0:17:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... No, I never said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.41,0:17:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm with you, I feel something...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.70,0:17:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.87,0:17:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.44,0:17:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they call it "sweetened?" {peace (of mind); tranquility; tranquillity; serenity} \NAll in all, a jolly good time. {/it's something fun}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My, I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was feeling the exact same way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.99,0:17:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.23,0:17:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unfair to have him all to yourself. {hogging; having all to oneself; monopolising; monopolizing}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.83,0:17:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.40,0:17:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, let's finish this talk inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.95,0:17:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad... Is really in love with Frau Gerlach?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.52,0:17:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean he is no longer \None bit concerned about mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.49,0:17:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.82,0:18:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand dad's feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.59,0:18:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But think of it - writing music just for children is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.07,0:18:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no benefit in the art that caters to kids. {there's no need in art that to flatter; to curry favor with; to curry favour with; to fawn on; to butter up to with children}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.93,0:18:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't seek benefit from it, Herr Fischer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.44,0:18:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate art is universally appealing \Nboth to grown-ups and to kids alike. {great; excellent; outstanding}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.73,0:18:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.10,0:18:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.07,0:18:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.30,0:18:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling sleepy already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.44,0:18:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, can we go home now? {unsure,maybe it's negative "ee" there}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.82,0:18:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I might need just a tad bit \Nof explaining left to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you find our society tiring?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I could drive her home, if you'd like me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.91,0:18:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... You'd really help me out by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you return without me and go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dad's companions still need him \Nto figure out all those complex matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.04,0:18:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.63,0:19:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, this feels like a strange house. {no clue what is yozo there, maybe "night sky" but that's a strage thing to attribute to a house: somehow, the house of the night sky I don't know}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.25,0:19:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time I feel this way \Never since I came to Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.87,0:19:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel lonely,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as if in this whole city, \Nthere's not a soul besides me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Fraulein?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you've been through something terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.51,0:20:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell by the Imp of Sorrow \Nsitting on your shoulder. {no clue what's kozou, has to be "youngster; boy; kid; brat", I hope they dont return to it later, would assume something like devil and angel on your different shoulders}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Imp of Sorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.49,0:20:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, with this guy around, \Nyou won't be able to get any night's sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.75,0:20:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But fine, this old Herr \Nwill look after it for you. {to look after; to take care of; to keep; to hold on to; to keep in custody}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.67,0:20:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And... got you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.00,0:20:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There, caught the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.91,0:20:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, he is not your problem now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.55,0:20:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to get a good sleep. \NYou'll be young and cheerful again in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.56,0:20:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, good night, Young Fraulein.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.22,0:20:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night! Thank you, Old Herr.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.36,0:20:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What just happened, Fraulein?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.72,0:20:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he want something from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, do you know who he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.80,0:21:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some painter, lives next door to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Has a reputation of an outcast and an oddball to boot. {hitozukiai is social disposition and I've no clue what it means; the whole sentence is "in exchange/place of bad/poor social disposition" and it's evn more cryptic; would assume kawarimono - "eccentric; oddball; character; weirdo"; hitozuki is reputation, so this starts to clear up}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.94,0:21:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, his name was something like Gabele. {from de}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.65,0:21:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise, I suggest you avoid \Neven an eye contact with someone like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.61,0:21:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right, I ought to get cheerful again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.89,0:21:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Having seen the dad's world, hidden from her up until now, \NLotte had spent this whole day utterly downhearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.67,0:21:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to the encounter with Herr Gabele, \Nher heart had become a little lighter already.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.21,0:21:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what other trials \Nmay be awaiting her in the coming day?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.31,0:22:12.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.84,0:22:16.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Comment: 0,0:22:15.37,0:22:15.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.30,0:22:20.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.02,0:22:22.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.15,0:22:34.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.57,0:22:38.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:41.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.87,0:22:45.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.71,0:22:48.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.29,0:22:51.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.84,0:22:56.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:23:00.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.09,0:23:05.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.74,0:23:09.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.15,0:23:12.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.78,0:23:15.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.60,0:23:20.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:23.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:23:27.37,0:23:27.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.65,0:23:29.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:34.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,Luise! I had found myself a new friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.52,0:23:36.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,It's a painter called Herr Gabele.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.19,0:23:39.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,Glad to know! Dad cannot even work from home,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.16,0:23:41.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,so Lotte might feel sad, being left alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.16,0:23:46.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why, while talking to Herr Gabele in his flat, \NI came up with this new great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.20,0:23:47.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.27,0:23:48.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Just pray for my success, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.77,0:23:50.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,I'll make them swap! Will think of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.77,0:23:52.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.67,0:23:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,New Ally, Herr Gabele. {新しい味方・ガベーレさん}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.17,0:23:57.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 20 \NNew Ally, Herr Gabele {新しい味方・ガベーレさん}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.94,0:23:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for it!
